Show HN: Bonito – the Hassle free text classifier in R
text:
For all tech-people and data-scientists out there:

I am happy to launch a prototype version of a text classifier in R. You can run the code locally or in a docker environment. I provide you with an example data set but you are welcome to use your own training data and and set your own labels.

I am happy if you use the model and give me feedback. I am also interested in what you have used the model for and with what data.

A star on Github always helps too!

Tell HN: Founders spam emailing their startups needs to be shamed and stopped
text:
Hi HN,

In the last couple of months I've received at least 5 spam emails from random people directly pushing their products in more and more aggressive ways. This seem like the kind sleazy marketing or douchy growth hacking tactics that are all around.

I just think this is appalling and it needs to be called out and shamed.

Here's the last one I got:

    From: Michael Schilonka <michael@blueshoe.io>
    To:
    Subject: Alternative to tilt.dev
    Date: 
    Size: 24 KB


    Hey xxxx, 

    I saw on Github that you are interested in tilt.dev.  I hope you don't mind me reaching out to you personally. 

    While we really love tilt.dev, we always had a few issues with it. For example Tilt does not create a cluster for you, so there is at least one more tool our devs have to deal with. 

    In addition Starlark, the Tiltfile definition language, is too complex for our taste and the recent acquisition of Tilt by Docker made us kind of unsure about the future of the tool. 

    Anyway, we came up with a new open source project called Getdeck that creates reproducible Kubernetes environments for development and testing. It’s a command-line application and file specification around the concept of a Kubernetes Deck. 

    I'd really appreciate if you had a look https://getdeck.dev/ 

    I'd really love to hear your feedback on this and maybe some input on if you feel there is something missing with regards to features, documentation or usecases? 

    Kind regards 

    Michael Schilonka

    Technical Director

    BLUESHOE GmbH
